    "headline": "TSMC Q2 revenue jumps 36% from a year earlier, beating market expectations",
    "summary": "TSMC, the world's ‌largest contract chipmaker, ‌reported on Monday second-quarter ​revenue of 1.27 trillion Taiwan dollars ($39.63 billion), beating market ‌expectations and ⁠rising 36% from a year ⁠earlier on surging interest in artificial ​intelligence applications. An ​LSEG ​SmartEstimate, drawn ‌from 20 analysts, had expected revenue in the April-to-June quarter of 1.264 trillion Taiwan ‌dollars. Taiwan Semiconductor ​Manufacturing Co (TSMC) ​is ​a major ‌supplier to companies including ​Nvidia ​and Apple.",
